# Architecture & Boundaries (must follow)

- Use a provider-agnostic core:
  - "Core domain" defines tasks, prompt candidates, runs, and iterations.
  - "Provider adapters" implement calling external model APIs.
- Separate prompt-generation from output-generation:
  - Prompt generator: produces candidate prompts (N=20 first, M=10 next).
  - Runner: executes candidates to produce outputs.
  - They may use the same provider, but keep interfaces separate.

Data model (conceptual):
- Project/Session
- Task
- Input(s): optional image + text context
- CandidatePrompt
- RunResult (per candidate per model)
- Feedback: selected candidates + notes
- Iteration: batches linked together

UI responsibilities:
- Never let UI talk directly to providers.
- UI calls Next.js API routes (or server actions) only.
